An application for a certification of a class action to be brought against Tiger Brands and Enterprise Foods has been filed in the South Gauteng High Court in Johannesburg. Lead attorney on the action suit Thamsanqa Malusi from Richard Spoor Attorneys said the class action suit relates to the listeriosis outbreak which claimed the lives of at least 180 South Africans after they consumed products including polony, viennas and russians. More to follow. Source: News24